raw_data.name: CrossRidge Cafe
raw_data.full_address: 2001 Parkway Dr, Indian Land, SC 29707, United States
raw_data.typical_time_spent: People typically spend up to 2.5 hours here

reviews_data.review_text: Great venue, great service, and great food. Great specials too.

review_questions.Seating type: Indoor dining area, Private dining room

reviews_data.review_text: They have a wonderful appreciation for our military veterans (past, present, and future ).

I so enjoy the cozy atmosphere with good food, cozy nooks to read a book on the shelf, visit with a friend or play games at their many tables, or stroll through the lovely gardens outside! What a treat!

Awesome atmosphere!  What a wonderful setting for a quiet lunch with a friend.  Absolutely the BEST chicken salad I have ever had.  What a find!!  I am so grateful to have discovered this place in my own backyard!!
Gave up after 40 minutes waiting for my sandwich
Big. Inside and outside
Everyone had a great lunch. There were 5 of us. Service was a bit slow but pleasant. Salads and sandwiches were generous in size, fresh and delish. Hours are limited so check before you go.
CrossRidge Cafe is such a unique place. The food is great, the atmosphere is welcoming, and cozy seating options are abundant. I have recommended it to many friends.
Very affordable and nice atmosphere!
Very nice place for a reasonably priced lunch.  Food was very good

This cafe is inside a church so its spacious, plenty of seating, and its never bombarding patrons with loud music. Lots of fun original coffee drinks; I've tried a different one everything I've visited. There's also a lot of books patrons can read if that's your thing. Really nice pond outside so depending on where you are sitting the view is really nice. Restroom is super clean. The whole place is clean, in fact. Team does a good job.
people are very nice. very nice sitting area. family friendly. espresso had a burnt bean taste (reason of 3 stars). I plan to try their another type of coffee later.
Beautiful spot to relax and enjoy a coffee or a bite to eat. Lovely, friendly service. Thank you!
Friendly staff, reasonable prices.  Generous portions.  Chicken salad is amazing.
Excelente
A best kept secret! I had the best chicken salad wrap I've eaten in a long time. The service was quick and the atmosphere was quiet and relaxing. I'll be back!
I love their coffee so much!
Cioncidentally discovered this place and I am sooo happy🪷 Wonderful vibe looking into a small man made pond. N8ce coffee and salads. I REALLY dont know why people go to Starbucks?!?
The prices are fantastic The flavor is great the coffee is delicious. The atmosphere is peaceful and respectful.
The staff are always very friendly. Great place to meet friends.
The staff are always very friendly. Great place to meet friends.
Such a wonderful coffee shop! Really great atmosphere 😊

What a hidden gem!! I was hoping for a decent cup of coffee and needed food but this place far exceeded expectations! The atmosphere seemed almost magical decorated for the holidays. The staff was so friendly and helpful with deciding what to try. The wrap I got was really good, made fresh and the coffee…. Wow! Best latte I’ve had in a while! Delicious and strong, just the way I like it!!
Love this place very friendly people
Love this cafe!

My favorite coffee shop of all time!!! Jim provides the best customer service and makes the most delicious drinks.  Prices are very reasonable and the vibe is great. So many different seating areas to choose from and beautiful views out the windows. My kids beg me to take them there on a daily basis (the smoothies are great as is waffle Wednesday). I definitely come here too much but it's so worth it! Highly recommend!

Good coffee, delicious food, and pleasant service.

Update: Jim is the best barista in Indian Land
Great place!!
Fresh and yummy food with friendly welcoming staff

So glad we stopped in here for lunch and some coffee. From the outside it’s easy to miss, sort of has a church looking vibe to it, but trust me when I say you should stop in. Their coffee is REALLY good. Better than Starbucks and way more flavor combo’s. The lunch was solid too, had a Greek chicken wrap. Plenty of different areas to go sit at, even had rooms you could reserve for free for meetings etc. Going back for sure.
Fun atmosphere, nice people, good food.
Light breakfast..lovely staff and beautiful facility.

This place It's a little Slice of Heaven.
Friendly service, coffee was great
The staff was amazing. The food was just okay.
Great place for a quick coffee, super friendly staff and wonderful surroundings.
Awesome coffee shop... incredible water fall...great bfast sandwich and muffins
Best place to gather for good food, coffee and sharing with veterans on each Tuesday morning from 7:30-9:00.  Veterans get free coffe during this gathering.
This is an amazing place to go and have a quiet lunch or prayer. Lunch is usually pretty expensive so it's always a splurge when I go. The lunch however is worth the price.
Best chicken salad in the south!
....just a great place...that's all.
Friendly and helpful staff.
Wonderful, joyful place  for coffee and something to eat. Very friendly,  social and beautiful environment!
Friendly staff.
Excellent smoothies and  service

Limited selection of Christian books. Coffee is OK, but certainly not quality beans--the brew is weak.
Beautiful views and excellent coffee!!

I absolutely love eating at the CrossRidge Café!  The chicken salad over lettuce is delicious.   If you need lunch for your staff or board meetings, I would give them a try; everyone who attends our meetings loves their food.
If you have a large group, I would  call them a day or two in advance when placing your order.
Julie Walters
I absolutely love everything about this cafe and bookstore. I love the coffee, the baristas, and the overall environment.
